A Raw karambwanji is a brightly coloured fish used as bait to catch raw karambwan. Players must load a raw karambwanji into a karambwan vessel and then use the vessel with one of the karambwan fishing locations in the north-east of Karamja to fish karambwan.

There are no quest requirements to obtain the item; however, raw karambwanji require a Fishing level of 5 to be caught. They are caught using a small fishing net, in the Holy Lake south of Tai Bwo Wannai Village and north-west of Shilo Village (fairy code CKR), granting 5 Fishing experience per catch, not per individual fish. The amount of karambwanji caught depends on the player's Fishing level, increasing every five levels. The exact formula is ⌊ F i s h i n g L e v e l / 5 ⌋ + 1 {\displaystyle \left\lfloor FishingLevel/5\right\rfloor +1} . Thus players will catch 20 raw karambwanji at a time with a Fishing level of 95 or above and will catch 21+ raw karambwanji at a time when boosting beyond 99.

Raw karambwanji can be ground into raw karambwanji paste, which is used in the Tai Bwo Wannai Trio quest.

Raw karambwanji may be bought from Tiadeche for 10gp each after completing Tai Bwo Wannai Trio. He stocks 50 per world.

Since raw karambwanji are relatively easy to obtain and are one of the only stackable fish (the other being minnow), they are ideal for feeding pet cats. For the same reason these are also ideal when fighting hell rat behemoths.

The bonus from Rada's Blessing will allow the player a 2% chance to catch double the amount of raw karambwanji (a player that catches 15 Raw karambwanji will instead catch 30).

The player can continue fishing for Raw karambwanji even if their inventory is full. They may still catch Raw shrimps but the Raw shrimps will not drop onto the ground or cancel the player’s current action.

A '''Raw karambwanji''' is a brightly coloured fish used as bait to catch [[raw karambwan]]. Players must load a raw karambwanji into a [[karambwan vessel]] and then use the vessel with one of the karambwan fishing locations in the north-east of [[Karamja]] to fish karambwan.

There are no quest requirements to obtain the item; however, raw karambwanji require a [[Fishing]] level of 5 to be caught. They are caught using a [[small fishing net]], in the [[Holy Lake]] south of [[Tai Bwo Wannai Village]] and north-west of [[Shilo Village (location)|Shilo Village]] (fairy code {{Fairycode|CKR}}), granting 5 Fishing [[experience]] per catch, not per individual fish. The amount of karambwanji caught depends on the player's Fishing level, increasing every five levels. The exact formula is <math>\left\lfloor FishingLevel / 5 \right\rfloor + 1</math>. Thus players will catch 20 raw karambwanji at a time with a Fishing level of 95 or above and will catch 21+ raw karambwanji at a time when boosting beyond 99.

Raw karambwanji can be ground into raw [[karambwanji paste]], which is used in the [[Tai Bwo Wannai Trio]] quest.

Raw karambwanji may be bought from [[Tiadeche]] for 10gp each after completing Tai Bwo Wannai Trio. He stocks 50 per world.

Since raw karambwanji are relatively easy to obtain and are one of the only stackable fish (the other being [[minnow]]), they are ideal for feeding pet [[cat]]s. For the same reason these are also ideal when fighting [[hell rat behemoth]]s.

The bonus from [[Rada's blessing 1|Rada's Blessing]] will allow the player a 2% chance to catch double the amount of raw karambwanji (a player that catches 15 Raw karambwanji will instead catch 30).

The player can continue fishing for Raw karambwanji even if their inventory is full. They may still catch [[Raw shrimps]] but the Raw shrimps will not drop onto the ground or cancel the player’s current action.
